com.binaryheart.common.security

Class PasswordUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.binaryheart.common.security.PasswordUtils

  • public final class PasswordUtils
extends Object
    PasswordUtils is a fast, simple, and lightweight utility class containing series of methods for creating, comparing, hashing and random generating secure passwords to be stored on database or used for other purposes. It uses Java's latest built-in hashing algorithms and is independent of any other libraries.

    For hashing, all passwords are salted and hashed using a selectable hash algorithm. The secure salted and hashed passwords are generated in the below format to be used in the applications as desired:

    algorithm:salt:hash

    The first part is the name of the algorithm, second section is the salt value and third section is the hashed value of the raw password and salt combined. The separator character is a ':' (colon character). The salt and hash are Base64 encoded at the end when generating the final hash string.

    PBKDF2WITHHMACSHA512:Gbf2cL/XUqItqaXr4P5//A==:tn2M44bFJBAGrMbvqlZB88KwtywIsRlGx8c5o25PdQ2RbOlum/1Oqz8jL3Rr31HW56Jv81HnhScpcCNZuF8AFA==

    See documentation for random password generation and other utility methods.

    Author:
    Farbod Safaei - farbod@binaryheart.com

      • hashPassword

        public static String hashPassword(String rawPassword,
                                  HashAlgorithm algorithm)
                           throws IllegalArgumentException
        Hash a password string based on the given algorithm from HashAlgorithm. A secure random seed will be generated each time and is combined with the raw password to generate a secure hash.

        Note: For better security, it recommended using one of PBKDF2 algorithms over simple SHA ones. MD2 or MD5 is not recommended at all.

        The output format will have 3 separated sections: algorithm:salt:hash, salt and hash will be additionally Base64 encoded.
        Parameters:
        rawPassword - raw password value in String format
        algorithm - A value from HashAlgorithm
        Returns:
        String representation of a hashed password and salt with the format of algorithm:salt:hash
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if rawPassword parameter is null or empty string

      • verifyPassword

        public static boolean verifyPassword(String rawPassword,
                                     String hashedPassword)
                              throws IllegalArgumentException,
                                     InvalidHashException
        Verifies a provided raw password (in plaintext, unsalted and not hashed) by salting and hashing it and comparing it to a target value (usually coming from database).
        Parameters:
        rawPassword - Raw password in plain text
        hashedPassword - Fully formatted hashed password (target) to compare with, formatted as algorithm:salt:hash
        Returns:
        true if password matches the hashed value and false if the password does not match the hashed value
        Throws:
        InvalidHashException - if hashedPassword does not have the format of algorithm:salt:hash
        IllegalArgumentException - if any of parameters are null or empty string
